<br>
(more info can be found here: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/Pets/Pets.htm">www.magecompendium.com/Pets/Pets.htm</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> )<br>
<br>
1) Types of pets and general info<br>
2) Dual wielding and weapon use<br>
3) Pet buffs<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 1) TYPES OF PETS, AND GENERAL INFO</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
FIRE-<br>
Fire pets have a very powerful damage shield, equal to the pets level+1, in hit points, so a pet that's lvl 24 has a 25hp damage shield. Fire pets do not taunt well, but when mobs are beating on them the damage shield really chews them up. Nukes from fire pets are quite powerful and are fire based. Unless mobs are beating on the pet, its main power, the damage shield, isn't being used. They tend to be weaker in melee, perhaps having low strength.<br>
Fire pets are immune to FIRE  attacks, and are often used on Rak Ashiir, a  mob in City of Mist, that casts a VERY nasty fire AoE that has a lure type resist, fire pets are immune to this, players will generally be fried, regardles of levels or resists.<br>
The level 52/58 fire pets are different, they have poor damage shields, but cast several types of spells. These pets are very good on mobs that cast (when you want them interrupted like the Sirens in Sirens Grotto), or on mobs who's armour class is so high melee attacks are less useful on them (like in acrylia caverns)<br>
<br>
AIR-<br>
Air pets cast a magic based stun spell, which is very useful, they also go invisible which may make them less likely to cause trains in dungeouns. Air pets taunt very well, because of the stun. Stuns can interrupt casters and reduce damage from mobs. The stun does no damage, except with 50+ pets. Lowish strength (higher than fire, lower than water/earth)<br>
Air pets are immune to COLD. <br>
<br>
WATER-<br>
Water pets regenerate very fast, they also have the most powerful nuke which is cold based. Very good for raw damage output. Only lower in strength than earth pets, probably the most damaging pet you get.<br>
54/60 water pets backstab, or quintuple hit from the front, so its important to get tanks to move so the pets on the mob's back.<br>
Water pets are immune to POISON.<br>
<br>
EARTH-<br>
Earth pets are very strong and cast a root spell, the root causes damage from lvl 50+ pets. They seem to have low agility so get hit a lot for more damage. Roots can stop runners, anchor mobs off casters.<br>
Earth pets are immune to DISEASE. They are very good for *chain casting*, where you let the pet die and cast another, etc until mob dies, the root hopeully gives you time to do this.<br>
<br>
MONSTER-<br>
Monster pets do not cast spells, they do not use weapons, they can sometimes damage shield themselves like a fire pet. They are good on mobs that spells won't affect, like Reavers in City of Mist. They taunt pretty good, and are very tough. they make a very good &quot;tank&quot;.<br>
Monster pets are immune to DISEASE attacks.<br>
<br>
EPIC-<br>
Epic pet is always lvl 49, hits for 67hp, procs 143hp cold nuke, casts 100hp(?) magic based stun 5 sec duration, 50 hp damage shield, taunts extremely well. High resistances to all attack forms (especially magic) but is not immune.<br>
<br>
<br>
It is important to note that because pets are low level compared to what they typically fight, using debuffs, so pets spells land, is a good idea if you have mana, or if the fight may be tough. Malise, Malosi etc are very good for letting your pet function better, this is very important on mobs you want stunned for example.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 2)  DUAL WIELDING AND WEAPON USE.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
From level 24 spells on, pets dual wield, give them a weapon, a summoned dagger is sufficient, and they dual wield. From lvl 39+ all pets dual wield without needing to give them weapons.<br>
<br>
Up to lvl 20 spells, pets can do greater damage if you give them  a large weapon with a big damage ability, like a rusty 2 handed sword or 2 handed axe. Do NOT give lvl 24+ pets 2 handed weapons as then they cannot dual wield and will do less damage.<br>
<br>
Pets cannot wield no-drop weapons, and wepaons with a specific class/race desigantion, like Weighted Axes (large race only). Pets can wield most weapons though,a nd weaposn with procs (effects) can be very good.<br>
NOTE: <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> The Sword of Runes only procs on summoned mobs, like elementals!</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Weapons for pets, in alphabetical order of expense/usefulness/rarity</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
a) Gnoll hide lariats&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp ---Proc a magic based stun, wielder must be level 25+ so pet must be from a lvl 29 +spell (almost max lvl 29 pet).  Can be found in Splitpaw, South Karana, perhaps Black Burrow.<br>
b) Tentacle Whips---Procs a lifetap that heals pet, found in najeena off tentacle terrors.<br>
c) Serated Bone Dirk---Found in Lower Guk from the Assassin, procs a Snare DoT.<br>
d) Polished Granite Tomahak---Procs a rune that absorbs damage, found in Highpass Hold, to the West from named gnoll.<br>
e) Kunzar Kujuch---Procs a Snare, found in City of Mist, random drop from any mob. Pet has to be from lvl 49 spell (54 or 56 hitter) or from 51+ spell.<br>
d) Short Sword of Ykesha---procs 75hp nuke magic based. Lower Guk from Ghul Lord. pet has to be from lvl 49+ spell.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 3) PET BUFFS</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
The Burnout series of spells mages get adds strength, AC and haste. Other classes shouldn't waste those kind of buffs on mages pets unless they are WAY higher level than you, or it's for a special use.<br>
Air and Fire pets tend to have low strength, so a strength buff  can be useful. Agility buffs are good especially on earth pets. Dex buffs increase the chance of weapons proccing if the pet has some.<br>
On major fights against boss mobs, putting some hit point buffs, such as Skin Like Diamond, Aegolism etc, may be good. If mobs use an AoE dispel that could strip pet buffs, put lots of &quot;junk buffs&quot; on first, these are simple low cost buffs that will get stripped off before the important ones, hopefully.<br>
<br>
